# Agent Commands Protocol

## Triggers & Command Dictionary
If the user mentions any of these commands in the chat, you MUST instantly adapt your behavior accordingly:

- **`КАИ`** (Код/Архитектура/Инфраструктура / Full CAI analysis): Perform a deep cross-check between actual code, architecture diagrams, and infrastructure settings. Find discrepancies.
- **`АИС`** (Arch-Scan): Read and apply the relevant Architecture/Infrastructure Specification (`docs/ais/`) before proceeding.
- **`ЕИП`** (SSOT Check): Verify against the Unified Source of Truth. Do not guess; find the SSOT file and read it.
- **`ФИН`** (Finalization): Run the Closure Protocol. Document all decisions, update skills/AIS, and prepare for task closure.
- **`ОМК`** (Answer Maximally Briefly): Respond in max 3 lines. Essence only. No fluff.
- **`ВЗП`** (Planned Execution): Default autonomous execution of a plan step-by-step.
- **`ФИНС`** (Discovery Blocks): Finalization of Discovery Blocks.

## Response Requirement
When you detect one of these triggers in the user's prompt, explicitly mention that you are executing the requested protocol (e.g. "Выполняю КАИ-анализ...", "Принято, ОМК: ...") so the user knows the skill fired.